    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-12-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-12-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="447"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d447">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.51 War Credits/682</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the Greek
                        Minister</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Simopoulos</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-12-07">December 7,
                            1934</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I am requested by the Secretary of the Treasury
                    to notify the Government of Greece that there was received on November 10, 1934,
                        <pb facs="0647" n="547" xml:id="pg_547"/> by the Federal Reserve Bank of New
                    York for credit in the account of the Treasurer of the United States, the sum of
                    $76,272 from the International Financial Committee, Athens, on behalf of the
                    Government of Greece representing a partial payment of interest due from that
                    Government on account of the 4% loan of 1929 made to the Greek Government by the
                    United States under the Funding Agreement of May 10, 1929.</p>
                <p>These funds were applied by the Treasury to the payment of 35% of the semi-annual
                    interest amounting to $217,920, due November 10, 1934, on the 4% loan of
                    1929.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>R. <hi rend="smallcaps">Walton Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
